## Phase 3 - Pressure-Only Consequences and Scrutiny Memory  
**(SUBSTANTIALLY COMPLETE)**

> **Purpose:** Let inspections matter through scrutiny and pressure only, while preserving the no-enforcement boundary.

### Implemented
- failed invalid inspections can increase customs scrutiny
- scrutiny persistence across save/load
- deterministic scrutiny decay over time
- deterministic recent-violation memory for Level 2 outcomes
- deterministic inspection-depth bias from recent Level 2 violations
- bounded pruning of stale scrutiny memory
- compact and deterministic customs log visibility for deeper audit summaries

### Current outcome model
- pass -> no consequence
- documentary suspicion or invalidity -> pressure and scrutiny consequences only
- no denial of sale, travel, cargo, or credits in this phase

### Remaining ambiguity
- recent run evidence is clear that pressure-only consequence mechanics exist, but runtime manual verification remains advisable to confirm the exact escalation matrix for Level 1 versus Level 2 outcomes under live play.

Status: substantially complete for the intended no-enforcement scope.  
Recommended next work is validation and tighter surfacing, not broader punishment.

